This wide ranging Palaearctic species is known from all stages. The aquatic larvae live in lakes, ponds, mud, swamps, peat-bogs and have also been reared from algae in saline meadows. The records from Finland (
Hackman 1980
), Italy (
Boorman et al. 1995
) and Denmark (
Petersen & Achim 2001
) are questionable because they did not contain locality data, and therefore, we have not included these countries in this section.
